0029   0000             
0030   0000             ;AVI ELF II, VIP Personality ROM, SD Card Reader
0031   0000             ;Josh Bensadon
0032   0000             ;Jan 9, 2024
0033   0000             ;
0034   0000             ;The AVI ELF II is Ed Keefe's reproduction of the Netronics ELF II computer.
0035   0000             ;It looks very similar to the orginal, but offers 32K of RAM and elevated 
0036   0000             ;Keyboard & Display boards.
0037   0000             ;
0038   0000             ;This ROM can make use of a VIP Keypad Personality module to run the ELF II
0039   0000             ;as a RCA VIP.
0040   0000             ;
0041   0000             ;The SD Card Reader will map this ROM at 0000 after RESET for boot.  
0042   0000             ;
0043   0000             ;During Boot:
0044   0000             ;0000-7FFF 32K ROM
0045   0000             ;8000-BFFF 16K MAIN RAM WINDOW (Bank switched for 64K)
0046   0000             ;C000-FFFE 16K BOOT RAM
0047   0000             ;FFFF-FFFF SD Card memory mapped
0048   0000             
0049   0000             ;RAM (Main board RAM)
0050   0000             ;8000-BFFF 16K of 64K BIG_RAM on SD Card Reader, four banks of 16K
0051   0000             ;
0052   0000             ;ROM will either load a file from the SD Card to the 64K BIG_RAM or
0053   0000             ;load the BIG_RAM with VIP system at 8000 (optionally with CHIP-8).
0054   0000             ;
0055   0000             ;When MAIN_RAM is loaded, the BOOT process will end with the remap the MAIN_RAM
0056   0000             ;to the full 64K space and execute at a selected location.
0057   0000             ;
0058   0000             ;This ROM code will first send a serial message through Q to say "Hi"
0059   0000             ;Next it will test if the VIP Keypad is present.
0060   0000             ;If Keypad is present, a check if "C" is pressed, if so, VIP software will
0061   0000             ;be loaded and ran (this emulates a VIP)
0062   0000             ;
0063   0000             ;ROM will serve as a serial monitor and will display files from the SD Card
0064   0000             ;Files will be displayed on screen through the Pixie chip.
0065   0000             ;The VIP Keypad will be used as input to select SD Card files.
0066   0000             ;If the VIP keypad is not available, then it will use the ELF II keypad.
0067   0000             ;To make ELF II keypad work on single key strokes (like the VIP Keypad), the
0068   0000             ;data available line from the 74C923 will be monitored by EF3.
0069   0000             ;
0070   0000             ;
0071   0000             ;Command prompt:
0072   0000             ;DIR - Directory
0073   0000             ;I - Initialize FAT, read root directory
0074   0000             ;B - Select BOOT RAM
0075   0000             ;M - Select MAIN RAM
0076   0000             ;S - Sector Read.  S [####]  Use 4 digit hex number for Sector to read.
0077   0000             ;    Sector is loaded into RAM Buffer at C000.  Each sector is 512 bytes
0078   0000             ;    If you ommit number, the next sector will be read.
0079   0000             ;D - Dumps RAM in binary format.  D [####] [/S]
0080   0000             ;    Reads which ever RAM is selected (BOOT or MAIN)
0081   0000             ;    When reading BOOT, the /S will read the Shadow RAM in place of ROM (lower 32K)
0082   0000             ;E - Edit / Write to RAM.  E [####].  Writes to selected BOOT or MAIN ram.
0083   0000             ;    Any writes to BOOT under 32K will go to the Shadow RAM.
0084   0000             ;X - Execute program in MAIN, BOOT or SHADOW RAM.  X [####] [/R/S]
0085   0000             ;    It will default to the start address of a HEX file or allow a manually entered address.
0086   0000             ;    Switch /R will select BOOT RAM space.  /R/S will select the SHADOW RAM (lower 32K)
0087   0000             ;CD- Change Directory.  CD [dirname]
0088   0000             ;    Use CD .. to go to parrent directoy
0089   0000             ;    Use CD \  for root directory
0090   0000             ;V - View File on the SD Card.  V filename [/A | /H | /B]
0091   0000             ;    File is understood to be ASCII if the extension is .TXT, Intel HEX if .HEX or just
0092   0000             ;    Binary if .BIN or alternately B## where ## is a valid 2 digit hex page.
0093   0000             ;    /A will override the extension and force an ASCII dump
0094   0000             ;    /H will override with HEX (just the same as ASCII)
0095   0000             ;    /B will override with Binary
0096   0000             ;L - Load File on the SD Card.  L filename [####] [/A | /H | /B] [/R]
0097   0000             ;    /A, /H, /B will override the file type
0098   0000             ;    ASCII or BINARY files will load at ####.
0099   0000             ;    Binary files with the extension B## will load at page ##
0100   0000             ;    eg. L pattern.b2a will load at page 2A00
0101   0000             ;    /R will save the file to BOOT RAM space
0102   0000             ;    HEX files will always load at the addresses given in the file
0103   0000             ;
0104   0000             ;
0105   0000             ;
0106   0000             ;VIP Keypad will pull /EF3 line low when addressing a key down.  
0107   0000             ;0-F must be scanned by OUT 2
0108   0000             ;
0109   0000             ;ELF II Keypad will pull /EF3 line high when a key is down.
0110   0000             ;Key can be read as low nibble from INP 4
0111   0000             ;
0112   0000             ;CONTROL BYTE - OUT 5
0113   0000             ;High nibble selects the bit, low bit selects set/reset
0114   0000             ;
0115   0000             ;3 bits select EF4 connections
0116   0000             ;
0117   0000             ;30 - SD Write LED ON
0118   0000             ;31 - SD Write LED OFF
0119   0000             ;
0120   0000             ;
0121   0000             ;This code is for the 4051 production board
0122   0000             ;
0123   0000             ;
0124   0000             ;20/10/00 = 000 - not connected 
0125   0000             ;20/10/01 = 001 - EF4 x45 VIP KP Detect
0126   0000             ;20/11/00 = 010 - EF4 x47 ELF Keypad
0127   0000             ;20/11/01 = 011 - EF4 x47 ELF Keypad
0128   0000             ;21/10/00 = 100 - not connected
0129   0000             ;21/10/01 = 101 - EF4 Card Write Protect Sense Switch
0130   0000             ;21/11/00 = 110 - EF4 Card Detect
0131   0000             ;21/11/01 = 111 - EF4 Card Detect
0132   0000             ;
0133   0000             ;
0134   0000             ;Test VIP Keypad present - Bus Pin x45 VIP KP Detect connected to /EF4
0135   0000             ;BN4 Branches if NOT present
0136   0000             ;
0137   0000             ;
0138   0000             ;Test ELF Keypad present - Bus Pin x47 74C923 Strobe connected to /EF4
0139   0000             ;     /Q Pulls line for open test.
0140   0000             ;     Test with Q LOW (/Q=HIGH)
0141   0000             ;       -/EF3 low, B3 branches, ELF Keyboard present (strobe is holding low)
0142   0000             ;       -/EF3 high, Either no Keyboard or a Key is pressed, need to test with Q low
0143   0000             ;       Test with Q HIGH
0144   0000             ;         -/EF4 low, B3 branches, = no 74C923 chip (line is floating)
0145   0000             ;	  -/EF4 high, 74C923 strobe is high, means a key is pressed.
0146   0000             ;
0147   0000             ;     Continue control connection to x47 if ELF Keyboard is to be used, single keys are detected by /EF4
0148   0000             ;
0149   0000             ;
0150   0000             ;30 - DSR OFF
0151   0000             ;31 - DSR ON
0152   0000             ;
0153   0000             ;40 - \/ MAIN RAM Bank 0
0154   0000             ;50 - /\
0155   0000             ;
0156   0000             ;41 - \/ MAIN RAM Bank 1
0157   0000             ;50 - /\
0158   0000             ;
0159   0000             ;40 - \/ MAIN RAM Bank 2
0160   0000             ;51 - /\
0161   0000             ;
0162   0000             ;41 - \/ MAIN RAM Bank 3
0163   0000             ;51 - /\
0164   0000             ;
0165   0000             ;60 - ROM Selected (in bottom 32K)
0166   0000             ;61 - BOOT RAM selected (in bottom 32K)
0167   0000             ;
0168   0000             ;70 - SD Card Deselect
0169   0000             ;71 - SD Card Select
0170   0000             ;
0171   0000             ;
0172   0000             ;Logic of ROM code:
0173   0000             ;Start:
0174   0000             ; Say "Hi" to Serial output
0175   0000             ; IF VIP Keypad present THEN
0176   0000             ;    IF VIP Keypad C pressed THEN 
0177   0000             ;       Say "Running VIP"
0178   0000             ;       Load VIP to 8000 and RUN it
0179   0000             ;    END IF
0180   0000             ; END IF
0181   0000             ; Test Pixie Present
0182   0000             ; Start Pixie if present
0183   0000             ; TEST 8K RAM & Say results
0184   0000             ; IF VIP Keypad present THEN
0185   0000             ;    Say VIP Keypad present
0186   0000             ;    Select RX routine that scans VIP Keypad
0187   0000             ; ELSEIF ELF Keypad present THEN
0188   0000             ;    Say ELF Keypad present
0189   0000             ;    Select RX routine that scan ELF Keypad
0190   0000             ; ELSE
0191   0000             ;    Say no Keypad detected
0192   0000             ; ENDIF
0193   0000             ; 
0194   0000             ;
0195   0000             ; If Keypad and PIXIE is present, then the option to run from Keypad or Serial is available.
0196   0000             ; Otherwise, user can only work through the Serial.
0197   0000             ; 
0198   0000             ;
0199   0000             ;
0200   0000             ;This source file is assembled using TASM
0201   0000             ;
0202   0000             ;	Examples of coding pseudo ops
0203   0000             ;
0204   0000             ;	These Defines set pseudo op codes
0205   0000             ;
0206   0000             
